     1|/**
     2| * IVX AI Multi-Provider Fallback Chain
     3| *
     4| * Adds a safe, opt-in fallback abstraction around `requestIVXAIText`. The
     5| * primary provider stays the existing Vercel AI Gateway path
     6| * (`AI_GATEWAY_API_KEY`). Fallbacks are ONLY registered when their
     7| * provider-specific env var is set; otherwise the chain is a no-op and the
     8| * caller still sees the original primary failure.
     9| *
    10| * Hard rules:
    11| *   - never log API keys, never log prompt content, never echo bodies
    12| *   - never return secret values from the status endpoint (name + status only)
    13| *   - never invoke a fallback unless its env key exists
    14| *   - never use a fallback for streaming (yet) — only for completion replies
    15| *   - classified failures (auth/quota/timeout/network/unknown) so callers can
    16| *     decide policy; only retryable classes trigger fallback
