     1|/**
     2| * IVX Pre-Execution Feasibility Gate — truth-first execution gate.
     3| *
     4| * Runs BEFORE any tool execution, patch, commit, deploy, database migration, or
     5| * proof claim. Decomposes a task into required capabilities, verifies each one
     6| * against the real runtime, and returns BLOCKED with the exact blocker code if
     7| * any capability cannot actually be exercised right now. Only when every check
     8| * passes does the gate return READY and allow execution to proceed.
     9| *
    10| * Design rules (owner spec — FINAL PRE-EXECUTION FEASIBILITY GATE):
    11| *  1. Never reads credentials from chat history; only from the secure vault /
    12| *     Render env / approved backend runtime secret store (via ivx-secure-vault).
    13| *  2. Never prints secret values — only exists / length / masked prefix /
    14| *     auth status / HTTP status.
    15| *  3. If any check fails: STATE = BLOCKED with BLOCKER_CODE + exact blocker.
    16| *     No fake reports, no looping, no continuation.
    17| *  4. Spin-loop prevention: a blocker that repeats 2 times is remembered and
    18| *     the gate refuses to re-run it until the owner clears the memory.
    19| *  5. No VERIFIED status without a real proof ledger entry.
    20| *
    21| * Pure + deterministic apart from the live credential probes, which are
    22| * injectable so the module is fully unit-testable.
    23| */
    24|
    25|import { getVaultValue, inspectVaultVariable } from './ivx-secure-vault';
    26|
    27|export const IVX_PRE_EXECUTION_FEASIBILITY_GATE_MARKER =
    28|  'ivx-pre-execution-feasibility-gate-2026-07-05-v1';
    29|
    30|// ─── Capability catalogue ────────────────────────────────────────────
    31|
