// Spin-loop guard: if any blocker has recurred >= threshold times for an
// OWNER-authenticated request, refuse to re-run. This prevents the owner from
// looping on the same blocker. 
//
// CRITICAL: OWNER_SESSION_MISSING is NOT a spin-loop when ownerSessionPresent
// is false — it is the expected state for public/unauthenticated chat. Recording
// it in blocker memory caused the gate to block ALL subsequent requests
// (including normal AI questions) after two developer requests hit the gate
// from public chat. The spin-loop guard now ONLY fires for blockers that are
// NOT OWNER_SESSION_MISSING, or when ownerSessionPresent is true.

